attribute.description: Specifies how much space should be left side of the table and left-hand side of the leftmost column, similarly for right, top and bottom of the table.

attribute.description: Specifies the amount of space between the border of the cell and its contents.

attribute.name: panelClass
attribute.description: Class name of the CSS style to be used for the entire panel.

attribute.name: headerClass
attribute.description: If present, this attribute indicates that the first child component should be treated as a table header, rendered with the specified CSS style, instead of being rendered as a normal grid cell.

attribute.name: footerClass
attribute.description: If present, this attribute indicates that the last child component should be treated as a table footer, rendered with the specified CSS style, instead of being rendered as a normal grid cell.

attribute.name: columnClasses
attribute.description:
Comma-delimited list of the class names of the CSS styles to be used for each column. If the number of class names on this list is less than the value specified for "columns", the pattern will be repeated for the remaining columns of the current row; however, the first column in each row will always use the first style listed.
Note that these styles are applied only to content rows, not to the header or footer rows (if any).

attribute.name: rowClasses
attribute.description:
Comma-delimited list of the class names of the CSS styles to be used for each row. These styles should specialize the style specified by panelClass (if any), because CSS cascading is performed. If the number of class names on this list is less than the actual number of rows over which the list is iterating, the pattern will be repeated as many times as needed.
Note that these styles are applied only to content rows, not to the header or footer rows (if any).

attribute.name: columns
attribute.description: Number of columns per row to be rendered. If not specified, the default value is 2.
